docker build: Build an image from a Dockerfile.

docker run: Create and start a container from an image.

docker ps: List running containers.

docker ps -a: List all containers, including stopped ones.

docker stop: Stop a running container by its ID or name.

docker start: Start a stopped container by its ID or name.

docker rm: Remove a stopped container.

docker rmi: Remove an image by its ID or name.

docker images: List all available images on your local machine.

docker exec: Run a command in a running container.

docker logs: View the logs of a container.

docker network ls: List all Docker networks.

docker-compose up: Start services defined in a docker-compose.yml file.

docker-compose down: Stop and remove all services defined in a docker-compose.yml file.

docker pull: Download an image from Docker Hub or a registry.

These commands help manage containers and images efficiently.